Common Endpoints
/actuator/health
Provides information about the application’s health.
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/health

/actuator/info
Displays arbitrary application info (can be customized via application.properties).
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/info

/actuator/env
Shows properties from the Spring Environment (e.g., configuration properties).
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/env

/actuator/beans
Shows all Spring beans in your application’s context.
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/beans

/actuator/metrics
Shows metrics data (e.g., memory usage, CPU usage).
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/metrics

/actuator/metrics/{name}
View specific metrics data by name (e.g., http.server.requests).
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/metrics/jvm.memory.used

/actuator/mappings
Shows the HTTP request mappings in the application.
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/mappings

/actuator/loggers
Shows and configures the log levels of the application.
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/loggers

/actuator/threaddump
Provides a thread dump from the JVM.
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/threaddump

/actuator/httptrace
Shows HTTP trace information (recent HTTP request/response exchanges).
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/httptrace

/actuator/auditevents
Displays audit events (if auditing is enabled).
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/auditevents

/actuator/scheduledtasks
Shows the scheduled tasks running in the application.
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/scheduledtasks

/actuator/caches
Displays caches in the application.
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/caches

/actuator/conditions
Shows the outcome of conditional beans and autoconfiguration.
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/conditions

/actuator/configprops
Shows all @ConfigurationProperties beans.
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/configprops

/actuator/shutdown
Gracefully shuts down the application. Disabled by default.
To enable: management.endpoint.shutdown.enabled=true
Example: http://localhost:8080/actuator/shutdown
